
[1]diversify

   DIVERSIFY, v.t. [L.]

   1. To make different or various in form or qualities; to give variety
   to; to variegate; as, to diversify the colors of a robe; to diversify a
   landscape with mountains, plains, trees and lakes.

   2. To give diversity to; to distinguish by different things; as a
   council diversified by different characters.

   3. In oratory, to vary a subject, by enlarging on what has been briefly
   stated, by brief recapitulation, by adding new ideas, by transposing
   words or periods, &c.
